02:10:55.195 --> 02:11:01.835
or just yourself if you're working on the same projects a year from now. And then rnv also has

02:11:01.835 --> 02:11:07.034
a caching mechanism that means that if you've already installed the package, it'll just you'll

02:11:07.034 --> 02:11:12.475
get that one linked into the library. So you're reusing things instead of downloading each of them

02:11:13.674 --> 02:11:18.315
fresh each time. So you're getting kind of the best of both worlds, you're in project isolation,

02:11:19.034 --> 02:11:21.514
but intelligent reuse of the things you have on disk.

